
# 🧠 Full Web Recon Checklist (Pentester Workflow)

## 🟢 Phase 1: Scoping & Target Definition

Before touching tools:

* Identify:

  * Main domain (e.g. example.com)
  * Allowed assets (bug bounty scope)
* Note:

  * Out-of-scope domains
  * Testing restrictions (no DoS, etc.)

👉 Skipping this step is how people get banned from bug bounty programs.

---

## 🌐 Phase 2: Passive Recon (Zero Interaction)

### 🔎 Domain & Subdomain Discovery

Use:

* Amass
* Sublist3r
* theHarvester

✔ Checklist:

* Collect all subdomains
* Identify IPs tied to domains
* Look for:

  * dev.example.com
  * staging.example.com
  * admin panels

---

### 🛰️ Asset Discovery (External View)

Use:

* Shodan
* Censys

✔ Checklist:

* Open ports exposed publicly
* Misconfigured services
* Old servers still online

---

### 👤 OSINT (People & Leaks)

Use:

* SpiderFoot
* Have I Been Pwned

✔ Checklist:

* Employee emails
* Leaked credentials
* GitHub repos / exposed keys

---

## 🟡 Phase 3: Active Recon (Careful Interaction)

### 🔍 Port & Service Scanning

Use:

* Nmap

✔ Checklist:

* Open ports (80, 443, 8080, 22, etc.)
* Service versions
* OS detection

---

### 🌍 Web Technology Fingerprinting

Use:

* Wappalyzer
* WhatWeb

✔ Checklist:

* CMS (WordPress, Joomla, etc.)
* Frameworks (React, Angular)
* Server type (Apache, Nginx)

---

### 📂 Directory & Endpoint Discovery

Use:

* Gobuster
* Dirb

✔ Checklist:

* Hidden directories (/admin, /backup, /test)
* API endpoints (/api/v1/)
* Old versions (/v1/, /old/)

---

## 🔵 Phase 4: Deep Enumeration

### 🔗 Parameter Discovery

✔ Checklist:

* URL parameters (?id=, ?user=)
* Hidden GET/POST parameters
* API inputs

👉 Tip:

* Look at JS files for endpoints and secrets

---

### 📜 JavaScript Analysis

✔ Checklist:

* Extract:

  * API URLs
  * Tokens
  * Keys
* Look for:

  * Hardcoded credentials
  * Hidden endpoints

---

### 🍪 Session & Auth Mapping

Use:

* Burp Suite

✔ Checklist:

* Cookies structure
* Auth flow (login → dashboard)
* JWT tokens

---

## 🔴 Phase 5: Vulnerability-Oriented Recon

### 🧪 Web Server Weaknesses

Use:

* Nikto

✔ Checklist:

* Misconfigurations
* Default files
* Outdated software

---

### 🔐 Entry Point Mapping

✔ Identify:

* Login forms
* Upload features
* Search bars
* APIs

👉 These are your attack surfaces.

---

## ⚫ Phase 6: Organizing Findings (What pros do)

✔ Build a map:

* Domains → Subdomains
* Subdomains → IPs
* IPs → Services
* Services → Endpoints

Tools:

* Maltego

---

## 🧩 Pro Tips (What separates beginners from pros)

* Focus on **“interesting assets”**:

  * dev / staging environments
  * forgotten subdomains
* Always check:

  * JS files (goldmine 🔥)
* Don’t rush scanning—**analyze results deeply**
* Automate, but **think manually**

---

## ⚡ Simple Mental Model

Think of recon like this:

> **Discover → Expand → Analyze → Prioritize**

